Class FeedSynchronizationRelatedInformation

Represents information about related feeds or locations.

Inheritance

Namespace: Argotic.Extensions.Core
Assembly: Argotic.Extensions.dll
Syntax
[Serializable]
public class FeedSynchronizationRelatedInformation : IComparable
Remarks

In the case where a publisher’s feed has incorporated items from other feeds, it can be useful for subscribers to see more detailed information about the other feeds. In the case of feed sharing as envisioned by the FeedSync specification, this class can also be used to notify subscribing feeds of the feeds of other participants which they might also wish to subscribe to.

RelationType

Gets or sets the type of the related feed.

Declaration
public FeedSynchronizationRelatedInformationType RelationType { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
FeedSynchronizationRelatedInformationType

A FeedSynchronizationRelatedInformationType enumeration values that represents the type of the related feed. The default value is None, which indicates that no relation type has been specified.
Remarks

Publishers will generally include, in a feed, only the most recent modifications, additions, and deletions within some reasonable time window. These feeds are referred to as partial feeds, whereas feeds containing the complete set of items are referred to as complete feeds.

In the feed sharing context new subscribers, or existing subscribers failing to subscribe within the published feed window, will need to initially copy a complete set of items from a publisher before being in a position to process incremental updates. As such, the specification provides for the ability for the latter feed to reference the complete feed.

Exceptions
Type Condition
System.ArgumentException

The value is equal to None.
